Odaily Planet Daily News According to official news, Jupiter announced the launch of the token verification standard Jupiter Verify to provide the community with more certainty for new tokens. There are currently four types of verification, namely: 
1. Blue Chip: Applicable to tokens that have stood the test of time and are well recognized in the ecosystem, with a market value of at least US$100 million for at least one month, such as USDC, JUP, SOL, WIF, etc.; 
2. Community Assisted: Community Assisted type, suitable for new tokens and upcoming tokens with clear market and community appeal, such as JELLYJELLY; 
3. Social Media ID Verification: You can verify the ownership of your social account and submit a minting address to link the two; 
4. C.A.T Prelaunch Report: The relevant tokens need to review and publish a report on their settings before release.
